Description: Jacob persuaded to send Benjamin with his brethren into Egypt: a group of men standing around two men kneeling at center in front of a hooded figure at right; after Sir Anthony Van Dyck; in rectangular frame in imitation of a wash mount; from Tome II of CharlesRogers 'Prints in Imitation of Drawings' (London: Printed by J. Nichols and sold by J. Boydell, 1778). 1762 Etching
Producer name: Print made by: William Wynne Ryland
Curator's comments: For the accompanying text, see Vol.2, p.213 of the same publication. For a comment on Rogers 'Prints in Imitation of Drawings', see Hh,11.1.
Associated names: Associated with: George, 3rd Earl of Cholmondeley (?)
Acquisition notes: Purchased by British Museum Trustees in 1778
